      • make

        IConfigurationData make(UUID changeSetId,
                        boolean isSetIgnored,
                        boolean ignored,
                        boolean isSetInternal,
                        boolean internal)
        Allows creation of an IConfigurationData Object for use with ConfigurationAware Simple and Auditable IItems. Because this may be used to determine change from a previous IConfigurationData object, explicit isSet values are provided. A UUID changeSetId is required, even if matching IConfigurationData the UUID NULL_DEFAULT_VALUE_OBJECT, and so does not have an isSet option.

      • make

        IConfigurationData make(UUID changeSetId,
                        boolean isSetIgnored,
                        boolean ignored,
                        boolean isSetInternal,
                        boolean internal,
                        UUID configId)
        Allows creation of an IConfigurationData Object for use with ConfigurationAware Simple and Auditable IItems. Because this may be used to determine change from a previous IConfigurationData object, explicit isSet values are provided. A UUID changeSetId and UUID configId are required, even if matching IConfigurationData the UUID NULL_DEFAULT_VALUE_OBJECT, and so does not have an isSet option. The configId value is just for read-only. This value never saves in the database. TeamServiceContext always takes the precedence and only TeamServiceContext configid value saves in the database while saving the item.
        Parameters:
        changeSetId -
        isSetIgnored -
        ignored -
        isSetInternal -
        internal -
        configId -
        Returns:
        configurationData

      • make

        IConfigurationData make(UUID changeSetId,
                        UUID configId)
        Allows creation of an IConfigurationData Object for use with ConfigurationAware Simple and Auditable IItems. Ignored and Internal are assumed to be false and not set with this method. A UUID changeSetId and UUID configId are required, even if matching IConfigurationData the UUID NULL_DEFAULT_VALUE_OBJECT, and so does not have an isSet option. The configId value is just for read-only. This value never saves in the database. TeamServiceContext always takes the precedence and only TeamServiceContext configid value saves in the database while saving the item.
        Parameters:
        changeSetId -
        configId -
        Returns:
        configurationData

      • createIgnoredInternal

        IConfigurationData createIgnoredInternal(IConfigurationData configurationData,
                                         boolean isSetIgnored,
                                         boolean ignored,
                                         boolean isSetInternal,
                                         boolean internal)
        Allows creation of an IConfigurationData Object for use with ConfigurationAware Simple and Auditable IItems. Because this may be used to determine change from a previous IConfigurationData object, explicit isSet values are provided. If IConfigurationData parameter is null, the created IConfigurationData will have a changeSetId UUID and configId UUID as a NULL_DEFAULT_VALUE_OBJECT.
        Parameters:
        configurationData -
        isSetIgnored -
        ignored -
        isSetInternal -
        internal -
        Returns:
        configurationData

      • createSetIgnoredAndInternal

        IConfigurationData createSetIgnoredAndInternal(IConfigurationData configurationData,
                                               boolean ignored,
                                               boolean internal)
        Allows creation of an IConfigurationData Object for use with ConfigurationAware Simple and Auditable IItems. If using to determine change from a previous IConfigurationData object, explicit isSet values are not provided by this method and it is recommended to use a different ConfigurationData call.. If IConfigurationData parameter is null, the created IConfigurationData will have a changeSetId UUID and configId UUID as a NULL_DEFAULT_VALUE_OBJECT. This method explicitly copies the configurationData while setting the ignored and internal attributes, as a convenience method
